<div class="explanation">
    <h4><strong>What is Real Estate Wholesaling?</strong></h4>
    <br>
    <p>Real estate wholesaling is the most popular and widely-taught method of breaking into the real estate investing scene.   With little or no money down, you follow these steps: <br>
    <div class="internal-list">
         1. Put a property under contract for a cash purchase, usually a property that needs a lot of work or where the seller is in distress. (make sure this contract is assignable)<br>
         2. You  assign the contract to a cash buyer who wants to flip the property, who will pay slightly more for it than what you have it under contract for <br>
         3. All three parties directly involved in the transaction set up a closing date, and at closing you walk away with a check for the difference between the initial contract and the marked up price that the end user pays. 
            <br><br>
         <em>The wholesaler walks away with what usually resembles a profit (aka "finder's fee"), of about 10% of the initial contract price.</em>
    </div><!--end .internal-list -->
         <br>
        Investors like buying from wholesalers because they are experts in their market, they have a lot of properties to choose from, and the job of finding the deal is done for them.  All the investor has to do is flip the house for a profit.  <br>
        Find wholesalers in your market by selecting your preferred location above.
        </p><br>


